<br>
Now all this was deliberate, because the cherry in the bottle was a trap laid by a monkey-hunter who knew how monkeys think.<br>
<br>
The hunter, hearing the monkey's whimperings, came along and the monkey tried to run away.  But, because his hand was, as he though, stuck in the bottle, he could not move fast enough to escape.<br>
<br>
But, as he thought, he still had hold of the cherry.  The hunter picked him up.  A moment later he tapped the monkey sharply on the elbow, making him suddenly relax his hold on the fruit.<br>
<br>
The monkey was free, but he was captured.  The hunter had used the cherry and the bottle, but he still had them. &quot;<br>
-Book of Amu Daria<br>
<br>
